%%%
Hierarchical repeated-measures observation model.

Canonical SOTA pattern (Pyro `with plate` over groups + plate over
observations; Stan / Bambi random-intercepts model with per-group
repeated obs). Each of G groups has its own latent mean `mu_g`
drawn from a hyperprior; conditional on `mu_g`, the group produces
`N_per_group` iid Normal observations sharing a global sigma.

The forward model is `kernelof(iid(Normal(mu, sigma), N_per_group),
mu)` — a kernel whose body is an iid measure. Broadcasting that
kernel over the per-group `mu_g` values yields a [G, N_per_group]
observation matrix.

This is the motivating shape for fusion (b) phase F (composite
kernel bodies) — `matKernelBroadcast` today rejects user-kernel
heads whose body isn't a single builtin distribution.
%%%
flatppl_compat = "0.1"

% Group-level latent means (one per group, drawn from a hyperprior).
G = 4
N_per_group = 5
mu_g ~ iid(Normal(0, 10), G)

% Shared global noise.
sigma_g ~ truncate(Normal(0, 1), interval(0, inf))

% Per-group obs kernel: given a group's mean and the shared sigma,
% produce N_per_group iid Normal draws.
group_kernel = kernelof(iid(Normal(mu, sigma_g), N_per_group), mu)

% Broadcast the kernel over each group's mu — yields a [G, N_per_group]
% observation matrix per atom.
obs = broadcast(group_kernel, mu = mu_g)
